---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Terminal from '../components/Terminal.astro';
import InteractiveTerminal from '../components/InteractiveTerminal.astro';
import MultiAgentChat from '../components/MultiAgentChat.astro';
---

<Layout 
    title="DeJon Gaines | Technology Transformation Leader" 
    description="Challenging how enterprises think about technology transformation"
>
  <!-- Navigation -->
  <nav>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="nav-content">
        <a href="/" class="logo">DG</a>
        <div class="nav-links">
          <a href="#about">About</a>
          <a href="#focus">Current Focus</a>
          <a href="#lab">AI Lab</a>
          <a href="#engage">Connect</a>
          <button id="theme-toggle" class="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle dark mode">üåô</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-grid">
          <div class="hero-content">
            <h1><span class="gradient-name">DeJon Gaines</span></h1>
            <div class="subtitle">Technology Transformation Leader</div>
            <p class="tagline">
              Digital transformation used to mean 18-month roadmaps and PowerPoint milestones. Now I'm seeing enterprises generate measurable value in days, sometimes hours. That shift changes everything about how leaders should think about AI investment.
            </p>
            <div class="impact-areas">
              <span class="impact-item">Rapid Value Delivery</span>
<span class="impact-item">AI at Scale</span>
<span class="impact-item">Culture & Change</span>
<span class="impact-item">Executive Leadership</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-cta">
              <a href="#about" class="btn btn-primary">About Me</a>
              <a href="#engage" class="btn btn-outline">Let's Talk</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-terminal">
            <Terminal />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about" style="background: var(--bg-secondary); padding: 4rem 0;">
      <div class="container">
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 400px 1fr; gap: 4rem; max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; align-items: center;">
          
          <img src="/profile2.JPEG" alt="DeJon Gaines preparing for interview" style="
              width: 100%; 
              height: 450px; 
              border-radius: 12px; 
              object-fit: cover; 
              box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
          ">
          
          <div>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
              My career began during a pivotal shift in technology: the transition from analog to digital operations in the early 2000s. It wasn't a single moment. It was a ripple that spread across industries worldwide, reshaping how organizations operated. Watching that wave taught me that transformation is never just about technology. It's about timing, scale, and adaptability. That insight drives how I lead today: blending strategic vision with hands-on execution, validating emerging technologies before recommending them, and ensuring every initiative delivers measurable business impact.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; font-size: 1.05rem;">
              I've spent 20 years putting that lesson into practice across global operations, helping thousands of clients in commercial and public sectors navigate their most complex challenges. I thrive at the intersection of business and technology. Every transformation is an opportunity to learn, stay curious, and create lasting impact.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">
              üìç Lexington, Kentucky | üéì McKinsey Executive Leadership | üé§ Keynote Speaker
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Current Focus Section -->
    <section id="focus">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>What I'm Exploring Now</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          The questions I'm actively testing, and the conversations I'm having with leaders who want more than vendor promises.
        </p>
        
        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card-title">The Real Economics of AI Deployment</h3>
            <p class="card-description">
              	The cloud vs. on-prem vs. hybrid debate is missing the real math. I'm running my own infrastructure to answer the questions that matter: What's the actual cost per inference? Where are the break-even points? When does data sovereignty become non-negotiable? These aren't theoretical models. They're production workloads I can show you.
            </p>
          </div>

                   <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card-title">Why Culture Still Determines AI Success</h3>
            <p class="card-description">
              	Every company can license the same AI tools. The differentiator isn't technology. It's whether your organization can change how people actually work. I've learned that transformation isn't a technology problem. It's a behavior change problem disguised as a technology project.
            </p>
          </div>

         
        <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
            	These questions drive my keynotes, advisory work, and the experiments running in my lab. If you're past the theoretical frameworks and want a conversation grounded in what actually works, <a href="#engage" style="color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600;">let's connect</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
<!-- Upcoming Engagements Section -->
<section id="events" style="background: var(--bg-secondary);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Upcoming Engagements</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      	Where I'll be in early 2026. Exploring what's next, pressure-testing new ideas, and connecting with leaders who are building, not just buying.
    </p>
    
    <div class="card-grid">
      <!-- Event 1: Lenovo CES -->
      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #00a4ef;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üí°</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="card-title" style="margin: 0;">Lenovo Tech World @ CES</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0;">January 6, 2026 | Las Vegas, NV</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="card-description">
          	CES has always been one of the best places to see where technology is heading. What appears in the consumer market today shows up in the enterprise within 18 months. I'll be at Lenovo's Tech World event as part of their Customer Advisory Board, exploring their latest AI infrastructure and providing feedback on what enterprise environments actually need.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem;">üé§ Speakers: CEO of Lenovo, CEO of Intel, Chair & CEO of AMD, President & CEO of Qualcomm</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Event 2: Nexthink DEX -->
      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #00a4ef;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <span style="font-size: 2rem;">üíº</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="card-title" style="margin: 0;">The DEX Advantage</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0;">January 14, 2026 | Cincinnati, OH</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="card-description">
          	Digital employee experience is becoming central to how IT operates at scale. I'm attending Nexthink's event to explore their approach to automation and ticket elimination. Curious to see how their platform holds up against the operational realities of large, complex environments.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem;">üìç The Westin Cincinnati | 12:00pm - 6:30pm</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Event 3: Microsoft AI Tour -->
      <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #00a4ef;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <span style="font-size: 2rem;">ü§ñ</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="card-title" style="margin: 0;">Microsoft AI Tour</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0;">January 21, 2026 | New York City</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="card-description">
          	Microsoft is making significant moves in enterprise AI. I'm attending their AI Tour to see practical implementations firsthand and connect with leaders navigating similar transformation challenges. Less about the keynote, more about the conversations in the room.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <span style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem;">üìç North Javits Center</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-primary); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
        <strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Attending one of these events?</strong> I'm always up for a conversation with leaders who are building something real. Let's connect.
      </p>
      <a href="#engage" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

  <!-- AI Lab Section -->
<section id="lab" style="background: var(--bg-secondary);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>üß™ AI Lab</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      This is where I test what I talk about. A working multi-agent AI system running on my own infrastructure, with live metrics you can see for yourself.
    </p>

    <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <!-- Status Card -->
      <div style="background: var(--bg-primary); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border-left: 4px solid #1e90ff; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary);">Live Multi-Agent System</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          The AI landscape changes fast. Staying current means more than reading about it. I built this lab to explore multi-agent architectures, understand real-world performance, and validate what actually works before advising others. Everything here runs locally on a Lenovo PGX (NVIDIA DGX Spark) with no cloud dependency.
        </p>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
          <div>
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem;">ü§ñ Supervisor Agent</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem;">gpt-oss-120B orchestrates all agents</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem;">üíª Coding Agent</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem;">DeepSeek-Coder 6.7B</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem;">üîç RAG Agent</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem;">Document search with Milvus</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem;">üñºÔ∏è Vision Agent</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.9rem;">Qwen2.5-VL image understanding</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Multi-Agent Chat Component -->
      <MultiAgentChat />

      <!-- Info Notes -->
      <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-primary); border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #00d9ff;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0;">
          üí° <strong>What you're seeing:</strong>  Live telemetry from hardware in my home office. The supervisor agent routes requests to specialized agents for code generation, document retrieval, and image analysis. This is how I stay hands-on with emerging technology.
        </p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% {
      opacity: 1;
      box-shadow: 0 0 8px #00ff88;
    }
    50% {
      opacity: 0.6;
      box-shadow: 0 0 4px #00ff88;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .spark-dashboard {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
    }
  }
</style>



    

    <!-- Engage Section -->
    <section id="engage">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Let's Connect</h2>
        <div class="engage-content">
          <p class="section-intro">
            The best insights I've gained have come from conversations with people solving hard problems. If you're navigating transformation, exploring AI strategy, or just want to exchange ideas, I'm always open to connecting.
          </p>
          <div class="card-grid">
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="card-title">Speaking & Workshops</h3>
              <p class="card-description">
                I speak about what I'm learning: AI deployment realities, the culture side of transformation, and what it takes to lead technology at scale. Every talk is grounded in experience from real implementations, not slide decks borrowed from last year.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="card-title">Advisory</h3>
              <p class="card-description">
                I work with leadership teams who want a thought partner, not a vendor. Whether it's pressure-testing an AI strategy or thinking through a transformation roadmap, I bring a practitioner's perspective.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="card-title">Conversations</h3>
              <p class="card-description">
                Some of my best thinking has come from casual exchanges with peers. If something on this site resonated or you're working through a challenge, reach out. No agenda required.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p class="location">Based in Lexington, Kentucky</p>
            <div class="contact-buttons">
              <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dejon-gaines" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-content">
        <div class="footer-copyright">
          ¬© 2026 DeJon Gaines. All rights reserved.
        </div>
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/dejon-gaines" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>
          </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
  <InteractiveTerminal />
